  <h2 id="dsd">DSD</h2>
  <p>
    DSD files are decoded to PCM via DoP (DSD over PCM) for output to
    standard DACs.
  </p>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Format</th><th>Extensions</th><th>Engine</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>DSF (Sony DSD Stream File)</td>
        <td><code>.dsf</code></td>
        <td>FFmpeg</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>DFF / DSDIFF (Philips)</td>
        <td><code>.dff</code></td>
        <td>FFmpeg</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2 id="containers">Containers</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Format</th><th>Extensions</th><th>Engine</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Matroska / MKV / WebM</td>
        <td><code>.mkv</code> <code>.mka</code> <code>.webm</code></td>
        <td>FFmpeg (audio tracks extracted automatically)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>MP4 / M4A</td>
        <td><code>.mp4</code> <code>.m4a</code> <code>.m4b</code></td>
        <td>AVFoundation</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2 id="output">Output</h2>
  <p>
    All formats are decoded internally to <strong>32-bit float PCM</strong>.
    Output to hardware supports up to <strong>32-bit&nbsp;/&nbsp;384&nbsp;kHz</strong>.
    DSD is output via DoP. Gapless playback is guaranteed for all formats.
  </p>

  <h2 id="not-supported">What isn't supported</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>TAK</strong>: patent-encumbered; no LGPL-safe decoder available</li>
    <li><strong>SACD ISO</strong>: raw disc images. Individual DSF/DFF tracks play fine.</li>
    <li><strong>RealAudio</strong> (<code>.ra</code>, <code>.rm</code>): no LGPL-safe decoder</li>
    <li><strong>Encrypted files</strong>: Apple DRM (FairPlay) and WMA DRM files cannot be decoded</li>
  </ul>
</div>
